free_txt: FRM research reactor with 4 MW thermal power.
The detector was placed at a distance of 9 m from
the source, where the beam was collimated to a dia-
meter of 1.5 cm. The detector consisted of a poly-
ethylene sheet, 29.5 by 3 by 0.5 cm, inclined by 10
degrees in the beam line and of two thermal neutron
counters (enriched BF3 counters) on both sides of the
sheet. This arrangement was placed in the middle of a
polyethylene block with a wall thickness of 8 cm. The
block was completely covered with cadmium and located
inside a water container (65 by 65 by 65 cm).
